.TH ALICE-PKG 1 "2026-03-12" "Alice Runtime" "Alice Commands"
.SH NAME
alice\-pkg \- Alice OS package manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B alice\-pkg
search [QUERY]
.br
.B alice\-pkg
install PACKAGE[@VERSION]
.br
.B alice\-pkg
remove PACKAGE
.br
.B alice\-pkg
upgrade [PACKAGE]
.br
.B alice\-pkg
rollback PACKAGE
.br
.B alice\-pkg
list
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage Skill packages: search, install, remove, upgrade, and rollback.
All mutating operations are executed inside the engine process via Engine API.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B search [QUERY]
Search available skills in the remote store. Omit QUERY to list all.
.TP
.B install PACKAGE[@VERSION]
Install a skill package. Optionally pin a specific version.
.TP
.B remove PACKAGE
Uninstall a skill package.
.TP
.B upgrade [PACKAGE]
Upgrade a specific package, or all installed packages if none specified.
.TP
.B rollback PACKAGE
Roll back a package to its previous version.
.TP
.B list
List all installed skill packages.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR irc (1),
.BR self (1),
.BR engine (1),
.BR ctl (1),
.BR ask (1)
